{"word":"G5206 - υἱοθεσία - huiothesía - hwee-oth-es-ee'-ah - Adoption","slug":"G5206","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">υἱοθεσία</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>huiothesía"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>hwee-oth-es-ee'-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Adoption"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C5;&#x03B9;&#x0314;&#x03BF;&#x03B8;&#x03B5;&#x03C3;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B1; - uihothesia</b> - <i>hwee-oth-es-ee'-ah</i><p/>From a presumed compound of <a href=\"#/G5207\">G5207</a> and a derivative of <a href=\"#/G5087\">G5087</a>; the <i>placing</i> as a <i>son</i>, that is, <i>adoption</i> (figuratively Christian <i>sonship</i> in respect to God): - adoption (of children, of sons)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G5107\">G5107</a>"}]}